## Styling the Web
CSS makes HTML look good. We use it to change colors, fonts, and layouts.

```css
p {
  color: blue;
  font-size: 16px;
}
```

**What this code does:**
- `p`: This is the **Selector**. It tells CSS to target *all* `<p>` (paragraph) tags on the webpage.
- `{ ... }`: The curly braces contain the styling rules we want to apply.
- `color: blue;`: Changes the text color to blue. (Notice the colon `:` separates the property and value, and the semicolon `;` ends the rule).
- `font-size: 16px;`: Changes the size of the text to 16 pixels.

